00:05:10.090 --> 00:05:13.120
He was promoted to, um,
Private Second Class

00:05:13.120 --> 00:05:16.880
and he was initially encouraged
to rejoin his team in Afghanistan.

00:05:16.880 --> 00:05:19.420 position:56%
Um, an officer asked him, "Don't
you want to be a real man and return

00:05:19.420 --> 00:05:21.820
to Afghanistan with your unit?"

00:05:21.820 --> 00:05:24.760
But Faulkner, um, said
something that a lot

00:05:24.760 --> 00:05:26.910
of his fellow soldiers
didn't think was brave, but,

00:05:26.910 --> 00:05:28.760
in retrospect, was very brave.

00:05:28.760 --> 00:05:30.730
Um, he admitted that he
didn't think he was capable

00:05:30.730 --> 00:05:32.440
of going back into war.

00:05:32.440 --> 00:05:35.420
Um, he had too much going
on in his head, he said,

00:05:35.420 --> 00:05:39.360
too many voices, uh,
intense nightmares.

00:05:39.360 --> 00:05:43.080
An Army physician told him that he
had post-traumatic stress disorder.

00:05:43.080 --> 00:05:46.490
He was all ready to be fair
to the Army and had come

00:05:46.490 --> 00:05:50.820
into the Army all ready,
um, something, uh -- uh --

00:05:50.820 --> 00:05:54.250
in something of a precarious -- uh
