00:16:38.770 --> 00:16:44.910
I think we all know that our
veterans are among our nation's

00:16:44.910 --> 00:16:48.910
greatest and most valuable
civic assets.

00:16:48.910 --> 00:16:52.980
They are the backbone of American
society instilled with the --

00:16:52.980 --> 00:16:56.760
the values that most
of us aspire to, honor,

00:16:56.760 --> 00:17:01.620
duty, leadership, respect.

00:17:01.620 --> 00:17:06.040
We know that the vast majority of
our nation's veterans return home

00:17:06.040 --> 00:17:11.290
as leaders, part of their
communities, and valued members

00:17:11.290 --> 00:17:15.930
of our communities
leading exemplary lives.

00:17:15.930 --> 00:17:20.820
We also know that everyone's
journey home is not the same

00:17:20.820 --> 00:17:23.170
and some will struggle.

00:17:23.170 --> 00:17:26.980
We cannot ignore the fact that one
in five returning veterans suffers

00:17:26.980 --> 00:17:32.100
from PTSD and one and six suffers
from a substance use disorder.

00:17:32.100 --> 00:17:35.770
We cannot ignore the debilitating
effect of traumatic brain injuries

00:17:35.770 --> 00:17:40.900
and other trauma related injuries
on the lives of military families.

00:17:40.900 --> 00:17:44.980
We cannot ignore that these
issues often lead to homelessness,

00:17:44.980 --> 00:17:48.910
unemployment, arrest, or worse.

00:17:48.910 --> 00:17:52.140
If we do not intercept
these vulnerable veterans

00:17:52.140 --> 00:17:56.820
at the key moments of crisis, we
may not have another opportunity.

00:17:57.950 --> 00:18:00.650
Instead of sending
our veterans to jail,

00:18:00.650 --> 00:18:04.070
Veterans Treatment Courts ensure
that the veterans who struggle

00:18:04.070 --> 00:18:07.290
with the transition home become
involved in the justice system

00:18:07.290 --> 00:18:10.700
with a substance use disorder
and/or mental health condition

00:18:10.700 --> 00:18:14.480
or trauma receive the structured
treatment and mentoring they need

00:18:14.480 --> 00:18:17.240
to get their lives back on track.

00:18:17.240 --> 00:18:19.530
Veterans Treatment
Courts give our veterans

00:18:19.530 --> 00:18:22.750
who defended our freedoms
the opportunities to fight

00:18:22.750 --> 00:18:25.740
for their own freedoms,
freedoms from addiction,

00:18:25.740 --> 00:18:28.390
freedoms from mental anguish,
freedom from unemployment,

00:18:28.390 --> 00:18:33.060
freedom from homelessness,
and freedom from isolation.

00:18:33.060 --> 00:18:36.560
Veterans Treatment Courts recognize
that restoring our veterans

00:18:36.560 --> 00:18:40.170
to healthy citizens not
only honors their sacrifice,

00:18:40.170 --> 00:18:43.590
but it makes our communities
stronger.

00:18:43.590 --> 00:18:46.290
And Veterans Treatment Courts work.

00:18:46.290 --> 00:18:48.100
They work by reducing crime.

00:18:48.100 --> 00:18:51.430
They work by saving the taxpayer
a tremendous amount of money.

00:18:51.430 --> 00:18:55.680
And they work by returning health
veterans to our communities

00:18:55.680 --> 00:19:00.260
where we greatly need it -- they
are needed and where they belong.

00:19:00.260 --> 00:19:02.790
At Justice for Vets
it is our mission

00:19:02.790 --> 00:19:05.020
to put a veteran's
treatment court within reach

00:19:05.020 --> 00:19:07.750
of every veteran in need.

00:19:07.750 --> 00:19:11.020
Justice for Vets is the only
national organization committed

00:19:11.020 --> 00:19:14.500
and dedicated to the expansion
of veteran's treatment courts.

00:19:14.500 --> 00:19:19.850
And I am happy to say that
today there are 15,000 veterans

00:19:19.850 --> 00:19:21.460
who would otherwise be incarcerated

00:19:21.460 --> 00:19:23.970
who are receiving life-saving
treatment in the

00:19:23.970 --> 00:19:28.660
over 330 veteran's treatment
courts across the country.

00:19:28.660 --> 00:19:33.440
And, with that, I will
turn it over to you, Butch.

00:19:33.440 --> 00:19:35.740
