00:19:38.180 --> 00:19:41.000
Let me just briefly add my
thanks for the opportunity to be

00:19:41.000 --> 00:19:43.840
with you today and to offer
my thanks to all of you

00:19:43.840 --> 00:19:47.560
for joining this conversation,
a conversation

00:19:47.560 --> 00:19:52.300
that our nation must have about
providing a holistic solution

00:19:52.300 --> 00:19:57.010
to the challenges facing
some of our veterans.

00:19:57.010 --> 00:20:00.670
When a veteran and his or her
conduct brings them into contact

00:20:00.670 --> 00:20:04.390
with law enforcement and eventually
our criminal justice system,

00:20:04.390 --> 00:20:10.530
our nation, we, have a choice,
a choice between placing them

00:20:10.530 --> 00:20:14.860
in a criminal justice system
that may not have the capacity

00:20:14.860 --> 00:20:20.670
or the capability to consider their
unique experiences and challenges

00:20:20.670 --> 00:20:24.200
and a system where we are
likely to see them again,

00:20:24.200 --> 00:20:27.600
or we can make the
choice that because

00:20:27.600 --> 00:20:32.760 position:56%
of their service we are placing them
in a criminal justice environment

00:20:32.760 --> 00:20:36.480
where the unique background
and experiences are understood,

00:20:36.480 --> 00:20:41.360 position:56%
where the system melds treatment
with intensive supervision all aimed

00:20:41.360 --> 00:20:44.330
at improving outcomes, in
other words placing them

00:20:44.330 --> 00:20:47.540
in a veterans treatment court.

00:20:47.540 --> 00:20:51.570 position:56%
Veterans Treatment Courts, if
you're not familiar with that model,

00:20:51.570 --> 00:20:56.470
are a form of problem solving
courts akin to drug courts,

00:20:56.470 --> 00:21:00.750
which number in excess of 3,500,
and really have been a part

00:21:00.750 --> 00:21:04.470
of our jurisprudence since 1989.

00:21:04.470 --> 00:21:07.460
Problem solving courts like DUI
courts, women's drug courts,

00:21:07.460 --> 00:21:11.340
domestic violence and mental
health courts, to name but a few,

00:21:11.340 --> 00:21:14.260
all of which were created to
address the specific needs

00:21:14.260 --> 00:21:19.240
and appreciate the unique
experiences of their population.

00:21:19.240 --> 00:21:23.730
But it wasn't until 2008 when a
courageous judge and his staff

00:21:23.730 --> 00:21:28.250
in Buffalo, New York
recognized more could be done

00:21:28.250 --> 00:21:31.750
to improve the outcomes of veterans

00:21:31.750 --> 00:21:35.550
in their criminal justice
system and a movement began.

00:21:35.550 --> 00:21:37.860
They chose, again,
a matter of choice,

00:21:37.860 --> 00:21:42.290 position:56%
they chose to do something different
and started the conversation,

00:21:42.290 --> 00:21:46.870
a conversation today, which all
of us are privileged to continue.

00:21:46.870 --> 00:21:49.270 position:56%
Now I've been a part of these courts
since I retired from the Army three

00:21:49.270 --> 00:21:52.130
and a half years ago and
the Army taught me to kind

00:21:52.130 --> 00:21:54.780
of be a bottom line,
up front person.

00:21:54.780 --> 00:22:00.040
I have, however, spared you
the use of PowerPoint today.

00:22:00.040 --> 00:22:02.830 position:56%
But my bottom line up front is this,

00:22:02.830 --> 00:22:07.240
I believe that veterans
treatment courts, our government,

00:22:07.240 --> 00:22:13.720
the judiciary, and the community
at their very, very finest moment.

00:22:13.720 --> 00:22:17.830
In trying times, if you want
to believe in something,

00:22:17.830 --> 00:22:20.610
I urge you to choose
to believe in the value

00:22:20.610 --> 00:22:22.640
of the veteran's treatment courts.

00:22:22.640 --> 00:22:24.520
Now, there are a couple
of distinguishing features

00:22:24.520 --> 00:22:27.110
of these courts that
I'll highlight for you,

00:22:27.110 --> 00:22:29.320
special ingredients if you will.

00:22:29.320 --> 00:22:33.930
The use of volunteer
veteran mentors who choose

00:22:33.930 --> 00:22:36.360
to be a part of these courts.

00:22:36.360 --> 00:22:40.980
Trust me, no one responds
to a veteran like a veteran.

00:22:40.980 --> 00:22:44.530
No one cares for a veteran
like another veteran.

00:22:44.530 --> 00:22:46.550
They become their battle buddies.

00:22:46.550 --> 00:22:51.560 position:56%
The other special ingredient,
veteran's justice outreach officers.

00:22:51.560 --> 00:22:54.910
A great new story for the
Department of Veteran Affairs.

00:22:54.910 --> 00:22:57.450
These VJOs, as they're
called, sit in court

00:22:57.450 --> 00:23:03.810 position:56%
and almost instantly connect the
justice involved veteran to benefits

00:23:03.810 --> 00:23:08.590
and services that they
may not otherwise pursue.

00:23:08.590 --> 00:23:12.980
But why do I urge you
to choose these courts?

00:23:12.980 --> 00:23:16.250
As my colleague, my battle buddy,

00:23:16.250 --> 00:23:21.410
my teammate Melissa
said, because they work.

00:23:21.410 --> 00:23:25.550 position:56%
The data is now showing what we have
known anecdotally for some time,

00:23:25.550 --> 00:23:30.540
that trauma focused treatment
combined with the support

00:23:30.540 --> 00:23:34.030
of veteran mentors improves
outcomes dramatically

00:23:34.030 --> 00:23:37.120
for our justice involved veterans.

00:23:37.120 --> 00:23:41.760
And, importantly, these
courts restore home.

00:23:41.760 --> 00:23:44.220
They unlock potential.

00:23:44.220 --> 00:23:47.560
And they promote a
lifestyle of recovery.

00:23:47.560 --> 00:23:49.610
And as a nation are we really going

00:23:49.610 --> 00:23:54.130
to choose anything
less for our veterans?

00:23:54.130 --> 00:23:55.460
I hope not.

00:23:55.460 --> 00:23:59.230
I'm grateful for our panels
today and the information you're

00:23:59.230 --> 00:24:01.940
about to get from them who will
give up their time and expertise

00:24:01.940 --> 00:24:04.010
to help us better understand
and, thus,

00:24:04.010 --> 00:24:07.200
treat one of the unique
challenges facing some

00:24:07.200 --> 00:24:09.530
of our veterans and that is PTSD.

00:24:09.530 --> 00:24:12.540
The more we know and
the more we understand,

00:24:12.540 --> 00:24:16.520
the more lives we can change,
the more lives we can save.

