00:55:16.160 --> 00:55:18.380
in the same court that
I graduated from.

00:55:18.380 --> 00:55:21.120
I stick around there because
there's always a younger version

00:55:21.120 --> 00:55:23.340
of me coming through
the door every week.

00:55:23.340 --> 00:55:25.020
So I try to help them.

00:55:25.020 --> 00:55:26.490
I like to call it borrowed hope.

00:55:26.490 --> 00:55:28.600
I remember walking through the
door and not having any hope.

00:55:28.600 --> 00:55:30.790
And, um, you know,
people lend it to me.

00:55:30.790 --> 00:55:34.710
So I'm there to lend hope to the
veterans that are coming through.

00:55:34.710 --> 00:55:38.580
Um, I had seven arrests
before I ended

00:55:38.580 --> 00:55:40.480
up in the Philadelphia
Veterans Court.

00:55:40.480 --> 00:55:43.060
When I got into the
Philadelphia Veterans Court,

00:55:43.060 --> 00:55:44.360
that was my last arrest.

00:55:44.360 --> 00:55:45.660
I haven't been arrested since.

00:55:45.660 --> 00:55:48.610
I'm working on seven
years clean and sober.

00:55:48.610 --> 00:55:52.970
Um, it has absolutely changed
my life around to say the least.

00:55:52.970 --> 00:55:57.560
Um, I was housed in the
Philadelphia County Jail for a year

00:55:57.560 --> 00:56:01.060
of my life during, um,
several years of arrests

00:56:01.060 --> 00:56:03.830
and addiction and everything else.

00:56:03.830 --> 00:56:06.820
And, um, I am now in
