call, or what we call, alpha courts,

00:58:58.760 --> 00:59:00.560
the straight criminal courts.

00:59:00.560 --> 00:59:04.410
Um, each individual defendant that
comes before us we normally spend

00:59:04.410 --> 00:59:06.490
about three times as much time

00:59:06.490 --> 00:59:08.720
on each individual
defendant just engaging them

00:59:08.720 --> 00:59:10.880
because that's important
to the process.

00:59:10.880 --> 00:59:15.170
But the idea throughout the staff
with the mentors that we have,

00:59:15.170 --> 00:59:18.630
with the mentor coordinator, the
-- the probation department folks,

00:59:18.630 --> 00:59:21.350
the idea is to get them
through the program,

00:59:21.350 --> 00:59:23.790
the make them succeed,
to -- to salvage them.

00:59:23.790 --> 00:59:26.880
We initially started it, we called
it a human salvage operation.

00:59:26.880 --> 00:59:30.650
Unlike the traditional alpha
courts where it's more process.

00:59:30.650 --> 00:59:33.280
You might have three
cases set for trial.

00:59:33.280 --> 00:59:34.580
They're all going to settle.

00:59:34.580 --> 00:59:37.680
Everybody has an agreement in terms
of recommendation of the sentence.

00:59:37.680 --> 00:59:39.410 position:56%
And you're done in about two minutes

00:59:39.410 --> 00:59:41.440
and you got two minutes
more for the next one.

00:59:41.440 --> 00:59:44.600 position:56%
Well, you spend a lot more time with
the veterans and it's important.

00:59:44.600 --> 00:59:45.980
&gt;&gt; Jonathon Elias: And by the
time they get to you, Greg,

00:59:45.980 --> 00:59:47.370
some would argue maybe
it's too late.

00:59:47.370 --> 00:59:49.920
When they end up in the correction
system, but that's not the case.

00:59:49.920 --> 00:59:51.650
And a lot of times when
you're dealing with PTSD --

00:59:51.650 --> 00:59:52.950
and as we just pointed
out -- it's --

00:59:52.950 --> 00:59:56.560
it's an individual by
individual case basis.

00:59:56.560 --> 00:59:59.960
Is there a switch inside every
single one of these people

00:59:59.960 --> 01:00:03.610 position:56%
that at some point you can get to or
hopefully get to, flick the switch

01:00:03.610 --> 01:00:07.330
